## Title
[Specific — 3 to 10 words — name the board session (e.g. "Q2 Board Update — Strategy & Hiring"). Do NOT use "Board Meeting".]

## Summary
3-5 sentences: purpose, key resolutions passed, asks to the board, strategic signals.

## Detailed Notes
Narrative walkthrough of the board's reactions, questions, and points of emphasis. Attribute positions clearly. Capture push-back or concerns verbatim where important.

## Attendees & Roles
Board members, management presenters, observers. Flag conflicts-of-interest if any were declared.

## Resolutions Passed
Formal resolutions/votes: exact wording, who moved, who seconded, vote count (for/against/abstain). Populate `decisions`.

## Management Update
Business highlights, KPI summary, hiring, product, go-to-market.

## Financial Update
Revenue, burn, runway, ARR/MRR, gross margin, headcount costs, variance to plan.

## Strategic Items Discussed
Strategy, partnerships, fundraising plans, M&A, market shifts.

## Risks & Mitigations
Enterprise risks discussed — legal, regulatory, security, commercial, key-person.

## Asks of the Board
Specific asks made to board members (intros, customer connections, interview help, advice).

## Board Feedback & Direction
What the board advised or directed management to do or prioritize.

## Action Items
Populate `action_items` with owner (management or specific board member) and due date.

